Path: godot/classes/class_area2d.rst
Summary: This section describes the properties of the Area2D class, including angular and linear damping, audio bus settings, gravity parameters, and monitoring behavior.

Properties:
*   angular_damp (float): The rate at which objects stop spinning in this area. Represents the angular velocity lost per second. Default: 1.0. See ProjectSettings.physics/2d/default_angular_damp for more details about damping.
    *   Method: set_angular_damp(value: float)
    *   Method: get_angular_damp()
*   angular_damp_space_override (SpaceOverride): Override mode for angular damping calculations within this area. Default: 0.
    *   Method: set_angular_damp_space_override_mode(value: SpaceOverride)
    *   Method: get_angular_damp_space_override_mode()
*   audio_bus_name (StringName): The name of the area's audio bus. Default: "Master".
    *   Method: set_audio_bus_name(value: StringName)
    *   Method: get_audio_bus_name()
*   audio_bus_override (bool): If true, the area's audio bus overrides the default audio bus. Default: false.
    *   Method: set_audio_bus_override(value: bool)
    *   Method: is_overriding_audio_bus()
*   gravity (float): The area's gravity intensity (in pixels per second squared). This value multiplies the gravity direction. This is useful to alter the force of gravity without altering its direction. Default: 980.0.
    *   Method: set_gravity(value: float)
    *   Method: get_gravity()
*   gravity_direction (Vector2): The area's gravity vector (not normalized). Default: Vector2(0, 1).
    *   Method: set_gravity_direction(value: Vector2)
    *   Method: get_gravity_direction()
*   gravity_point (bool): If true, gravity is calculated from a point (set via gravity_point_center). See also gravity_space_override. Default: false.
    *   Method: set_gravity_is_point(value: bool)
    *   Method: is_gravity_a_point()
*   gravity_point_center (Vector2): If gravity is a point (see gravity_point), this will be the point of attraction. Default: Vector2(0, 1).
    *   Method: set_gravity_point_center(value: Vector2)
    *   Method: get_gravity_point_center()
*   gravity_point_unit_distance (float): The distance at which the gravity strength is equal to gravity. For example, on a planet 100 pixels in radius with a surface gravity of 4.0 px/s², set the gravity to 4.0 and the unit distance to 100.0. The gravity will have falloff according to the inverse square law, so in the example, at 200 pixels from the center the gravity will be 1.0 px/s² (twice the distance, 1/4th the gravity), at 50 pixels it will be 16.0 px/s² (half the distance, 4x the gravity), and so on. The above is true only when the unit distance is a positive number. When this is set to 0.0, the gravity will be constant regardless of distance. Default: 0.0.
    *   Method: set_gravity_point_unit_distance(value: float)
    *   Method: get_gravity_point_unit_distance()
*   gravity_space_override (SpaceOverride): Override mode for gravity calculations within this area. Default: 0.
    *   Method: set_gravity_space_override_mode(value: SpaceOverride)
    *   Method: get_gravity_space_override_mode()
*   linear_damp (float): The rate at which objects stop moving in this area. Represents the linear velocity lost per second. Default: 0.1. See ProjectSettings.physics/2d/default_linear_damp for more details about damping.
    *   Method: set_linear_damp(value: float)
    *   Method: get_linear_damp()
*   linear_damp_space_override (SpaceOverride): Override mode for linear damping calculations within this area. Default: 0.
    *   Method: set_linear_damp_space_override_mode(value: SpaceOverride)
    *   Method: get_linear_damp_space_override_mode()
*   monitorable (bool): If true, other monitoring areas can detect this area. Default: true.
    *   Method: set_monitorable(value: bool)
    *   Method: is_monitorable()
*   monitoring (bool): If true, the area detects bodies or areas entering and exiting it. Default: true.
    *   Method: set_monitoring(value: bool)
    *   Method: is_monitoring()
*   priority (int): The area's priority. Higher priority areas are processed first. The World2D's physics is always processed last, after all areas. Default: 0.
    *   Method: set_priority(value: int)
    *   Method: get_priority()
